stories.text:
It seems like everytime I visit Twitter, only the top or side menus show without any main content or tweets. I either have to do a force refresh or unregister their service worker and reload to get all contents to show.

Anyone else having this issue?

Are service workers really this hard to implement and get right or is the tech just broken?
stories.title: Ask HN: Are Service Workers broken or do Twitter engineers suck at them?

stories.text: One of the best tricks I have for debugging is putting a whole embedded interpreter in the middle of an interesting location in my Python code. Is there a similar trick I can do with C/C++? Or is there a whole different strategy that is even better than that that I should be made aware of?
